{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Lightly grease a large bowl with oil and set aside.","Place water, sugar and yeast in mixing bowl then warm <nobr>1 min 30 sec\/37°C\/speed 0.5<\/nobr>.","Add flour, oil and 1 tsp salt then knead <nobr>2 min\/<\/nobr>. Transfer dough to prepared bowl then cover with cling film and leave to prove in a warm place until doubled in size (approx. 1-2 hours). Towards end of proving time, preheat oven to 200°C and line a baking tray with baking paper then make filling.","Place spinach, ricotta, mozzarella, basil, garlic powder, remaining ½ tsp salt and pepper then mix <nobr>3 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>.","Transfer dough to a lightly floured surface, cut in half then roll one half out to 3 mm thick. Use a 10 cm round cutter to make 24 circles of dough, re-rolling any trimmings. Place 1 heaped tsp spinach filling in centre then fold in half pressing edges together tightly, tucking edges inwards to form a firm seal. Place on prepared baking tray then repeat with remaining dough. Bake for 8-10 minutes (200°C) until golden brown.","Transfer to a serving plate and serve while still warm."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["30 g extra virgin olive oil, plus extra for greasing","220 g water","1 ½ tsp sugar","2 tsp dried instant yeast","450 g strong white bread flour, plus extra for dusting","1 ½ tsp fine sea salt","160 g chopped spinach, frozen, thawed","160 g ricotta cheese","120 g grated mozzarella","1 tsp dried basil","½ tsp garlic powder","3 pinches ground black pepper"]}],"id":"r124151","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-vG3GkV6U-Ig\/XZaneC6vTJI\/AAAAAAAAg_c\/q1KG-JqY4ZUVlRnUv05Lc8ylGzKTsAaxwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_HcFHcsPyJdqVKdK5.png","title":"Mini Spinach Calzone","publishedAt":"2016-07-04T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"4.4 g","fat":"3.3 g","uom":"per 1 pieces","carbohydrates":"14.3 g","calories":"435 kJ \/ 104 kcal"},"usefulItems":"rolling pin, large bowl, baking tray and paper, cling film, round pastry cutte